According to the meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct draft, simple cocktails with 2-3 ingredients can be prepared in 10-15 seconds, while classic cocktails with 4-5 ingredients take around 30-60 seconds, and complex cocktails with 6-8 ingredients can take 1-2 minutes.

1. **More specific timing benchmarks**: Instead of providing a general estimate of 2-3 minutes, I will use the more specific timing benchmarks from the meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct draft.
2. **Accounting for cocktail complexity**: I will consider the varying complexity of cocktails and provide preparation times accordingly.

Revised answer:
The time it takes to prepare a cocktail can vary greatly depending on the complexity of the drink. Simple cocktails with 2-3 ingredients, such as a Gin & Tonic or Vodka Soda, can be prepared in as little as 10-15 seconds. Classic cocktails with 4-5 ingredients, like an Old Fashioned or Margarita, typically take around 30-60 seconds. More complex cocktails with 6-8 ingredients, such as a Pimm's Cup or Mai Tai, can take 1-2 minutes to prepare. It's essential to be patient and respectful of bartenders, especially during busy times, as they work to serve all customers in a timely manner.
